cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

The paper deals with image classification using deep neural networks and proposes a novel method to augment labels by exploiting word2vec representations. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves natural language processing techniques, which makes cs.CL (Computation and Language) a likely sub-category as well. The use of word2vec embeddings and deep learning models for classification also suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with face attribute classification, which falls under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
